0Lady%20Olena%20Zelenska.%20They%20received%20a%20standing%20ovation%20upon%20arrival%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20address%20at%20the%20Canadian%20Parliament%2C%20Zelenskyy%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20Russian%20aggression%20must%20end%20with%20our%20victory%20so%20that%20Russia%20will%20never%20bring%20back%20genocide%20to%20Ukraine%20and%20will%20never%20ever%20try%20to%20do%20so.%20Moscow%20must%20lose%20once%20and%20for%20all%20and%20it%20will%20lose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20started%20his%20address%20by%20talking%20about%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20world's%20first%20Holodomor%20monument%20in%20Edmonton%20in%201983.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20that%20time%2C%20Ukraine%20didn't%20yet%20have%20memorials%20commemorating%20the%20victims%20of%20the%20genocide%20of%20Ukrainians%20because%20Ukraine%20was%20under%20Moscow's%20control%20back%20then.%20This%20fall%20will%20mark%20their%2040th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20very%20first%20and%20important%20commemoration%20of%20the%20victims%20of%20Vladimir%2C%26quot%3B%20Zelenskyy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20said%20that%20a%20lot%20has%20changed%20in%20the%20past%2040%20years.%20He%20noted%20that%20Ukraine%20gained%20independence%20and%20dozens%20of%20countries%20recognized%20Vladimir%20(Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin)%20for%20the%20genocide%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20people.%20He%20said%20that%2011%20of%20these%20recognitions%20have%20been%20made%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20said%20Canada's%20military%20assistance%20so%20far%20has%20saved%20thousands%20of%20lives.%20He%20lauded%20Canada%20for%20imposing%20sanctions%20against%20Russia.%20He%20thanked%20Canada%20for%20supporting%20Ukraine's%20bid%20for%20NATO.%20He%20expressed%20gratitude%20to%20Canada%20for%20training%20Ukrainian%20soldiers.%20He%20thanked%20Canada%20for%20economic%20assistance%20and%20for%20helping%20Ukraine%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20Russian%20oil.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20President%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BMoscow%20now%20as%20always%20is%20bent%20on%20controlling%20Ukraine%20and%20makes%20use%20of%20all%20available%20means%20to%20do%20that%2C%20including%20genocide.%20It%20is%20genocide%20what%20Russian%20occupiers%20are%20doing%20to%20Ukraine%20and%20when%20we%20want%20to%20win%2C%20when%20we%20call%20on%20the%20world%20to%20support%20us%2C%20it%20is%20not%20just%20about%20an%20ordinary%20conflict.%20It%20is%20about%20saving%20lives%20of%20millions%20of%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20said%20that%20people%20will%20be%20winners%20in%20the%20war%20and%20not%20the%20Kremlin.%20He%20expressed%20hope%20that%20one%20day%20there%20will%20be%20a%20monument%20built%20in%20Edmonton%20to%20commemorate%20Ukraine%20and%20Canada's%20common%20victory.%20He%20ended%20his%20speech%20by%20saying%20%26quot%3BSlava%20Ukraini.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUkraine%20and%20Canada%20are%20the%20same.%20We%20stand%20and%20we%20fight%20for%20life.%20Ukraine%2C%20not%20genocide%20will%20be%20victorious%20in%20this%20war.%20People%20will%20be%20the%20winners%2C%20not%20the%20Kremlin.%20Freedom%20will%20be%20the%20winner%20justice%20will%20be%20the%20winner.%20You%20can%20know%20this%20for%20sure%20about%20us%20because%20you%20know%20for%20sure%20about%20yourself%20that%20you%20would%20never%20submit%20to%20evil%2C%26quot%3B%20Zelenskyy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECanadian%20lawmakers%20applauded%20following%20Zelenskyy's%20speech%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons.%20It%20was%20the%20Ukrainian%20president's%20second%20address%20to%20the%20Canadian%20Parliament%20since%20its%20conflict%20began%20with%20Russia%20in%202022.%20He%20had%20previously%20addressed%20the%20parliament%20virtually%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20Zelenskyy's%20address%2C%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20has%20reaffirmed%20support%20for%20Ukraine.%20He%20said%20that%20Canada%20will%20continue%20to%20provide%20economic%20support%20to%20Ukraine%20over%20the%20next%20year%20so%20that%20it%20remains%20a%20%26quot%3Bstrong%2C%20dynamic%20and%20prosperous%20democratic%20nation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20address%20at%20the%20Canadian%20Parliament%2C%20Trudeau%20expressed%20hope%20that%20Ukraine%20won't%20need%20military%20or%20financial%20support%20for%20long%20and%20that%20peace%20in%20the%20country%20will%20return%20soon.%20He%20called%20for%20opposing%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20rejecting%20his%20attempts%20to%20bring%20the%20world%20back%20to%20a%20time%20when%20%26quot%3Bmight%20made%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Canadian%20PM%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20continue%20to%20work%20with%20our%20partners%2C%20including%20within%20NATO%2C%20to%20provide%20unwavering%20support.%20We%20will%20continue%20to%20provide%20economic%20support%20to%20Ukraine%20over%20the%20next%20year%20so%20that%20it%20remains%20a%20strong%2C%20dynamic%20and%20prosperous%20democratic%20country.%20But%20our%20greatest%20hope%20is%20that%20you%20won't%20need%20military%20or%20financial%20support%20for%20long%20and%20that%20peace%20returns%20soon.%20But%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20a%20false%20peace%20based%20on%20a%20compromise%20imposed%20by%20the%20aggressor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BFor%20a%20lasting%20peace%2C%20we%20must%20oppose%20Putin%20and%20reject%20his%20attempts%20to%20bring%20us%20back%20to%20a%20time%20when%20might%20made%20right.%20A%20lasting%20peace%20must%20clearly%20establish%20that%20borders%20must%20be%20respected%20regardless%20of%20the%20size%20of%20the%20neighbouring%20army.%20This%20peace%20must%20restore%20the%20right%20of%20Ukrainians%20to%20determine%20their%20own%20future.%20Canada%20stands%20with%20the%20principles%20of%20Ukraine's%20peace%20formula.%20We%20believe%20that%20peace%20must%20respect%20the%20UN%20charter%2C%20be%20based%20on%20international%20law%20and%20preserve%20Ukraine's%20territorial%20integrity.%20This%20is%20the%20peace%20we%20must%20fight%20for.%20And%20that%20is%20what%20Ukraine%20has%20done%20for%20one%20year%2C%20six%20months%20and%2029%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20Canadian%20government%20will%20continue%20to%20support%20Ukraine%20%26quot%3Bfor%20as%20long%20as%20it%20takes.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20Canada%20has%20provided%20USD%209%20billion%20in%20military%2C%20financial%20and%20humanitarian%20support%20to%20Ukraine%20since%20its%20conflict%20started%20with%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETrudeau%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPresident%20Zelenskyy%2C%20I%20have%20clearly%20said%20that%20our%20government%20will%20stand%20by%20you%20for%20as%20long%20as%20it%20takes.%20Canada%20has%20provided%20nearly%20USD%209%20billion%20in%20military%2C%20financial%20and%20humanitarian%20support%20to%20Ukraine%20since%20Putin%20began%20his%20war%20of%20aggression.%20We%20are%20making%20a%20longer-term%2C%20multiyear%20commitment%20that%20provides%20predictable%2C%20steady%20support%20to%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20include%20USD%20650%2C000%2C000%20over%20three%20years%20for%2050%20armoured%20vehicles%2C%20including%20medical%20evacuation%20vehicles%20that%20will%20be%20built%20by%20Canadian%20workers%20in%20London%2C%20Ontario.%20We%20have%20also%20sent%20F-16%20trainers%20for%20pilots%20and%20for%20maintenance%20so%20Ukrainians%20are%20able%20to%20maximize%20their%20use%20of%20donated%20fighter%20jets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695430500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Ff65p2obg_zelensky-trudeau-reuters_625x300_22_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthis-russian-aggression-must-end-with-