ge%20for%20using%20his%20position%20to%20try%20to%20help%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBooker%20and%20Gov.%20Phil%20Murphy%20remained%20silent%20through%20Friday%20afternoon%20even%20as%20other%20Democrats%20began%20to%20speak%20out.%20Senate%20Majority%20Leader%20Chuck%20Schumer%20said%20Menendez%20had%20a%20right%20to%20a%20fair%20trial.%20The%20top%20Senate%20Democrat%20also%20confirmed%20that%20the%20New%20Jersey%20senator%20will%20step%20down%20from%20leading%20the%20powerful%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20committee.%20Rep.%20Andy%20Kim%2C%20a%20fellow%20New%20Jersey%20Democrat%2C%20called%20on%20Menendez%20to%20resign%20while%20he%20wages%20his%20legal%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20confidence%20that%20the%20Senator%20has%20the%20ability%20to%20properly%20focus%20on%20our%20state%20and%20its%20people%20while%20addressing%20such%20a%20significant%20legal%20matter%2C%26quot%3B%20Kim%20said%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20first%20reported%20by%20the%20New%20Jersey%20Globe.%20%26quot%3BHe%20should%20step%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20most%20notable%20sign%20of%20support%20has%20come%20from%20Rep.%20Rob%20Menendez%2C%20the%20senator's%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20press%20secretary%20Karine%20Jean-Pierre%20says%20the%20White%20House%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Ftherecount%2Fstatus%2F1705286247734817230%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Ewould%20not%20comment%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20situation%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20it's%20an%20active%20matter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20expected%20that%20like%20in%202015%2C%20Menendez%20may%20have%20to%20step%20down%20from%20his%20perch%20on%20the%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20Committee.%20Only%20this%20time%2C%20he's%20now%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20powerful%20panel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20sense%20why%20Democrats%20are%20more%20cautious%20this%20time.%20In%202015%2C%20then-Gov.%20Chris%20Christie%20could%20have%20appointed%20a%20Republican%20to%20the%20seat%20if%20M