.%20But%20I%20do%20think%20that%20will%20go%20away%20even%20for%20the%20ruling%20party%20after%20the%20election%20campaign%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWarsaw%20can%20%E2%80%98continue%20helping%20Kyiv%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELeading%20security%20and%20defence%20expert%2C%20Michal%20Baranowski%2C%20told%20the%20Associated%20Press%20news%20agency%20that%20Poland%20gave%20Ukraine%20what%20it%20could%20early%20in%20the%20war.%20With%20no%20plans%20for%20incoming%20shipments%20soon%2C%20Baranowski%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20see%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20fighting%20capabilities%20threatened%20in%20the%20near%20future%20%E2%80%93%20but%20still%2C%20he%20considers%20Polish%20Prime%20Minister%20Mateusz%20Morawiecki%E2%80%99s%20comments%20troubling%20for%20Kyiv%20as%20it%20seeks%20to%20shore%20up%20Western%20support%20in%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22162702%2F1079px-President_of_Ukraine_Volodymyr_Zelenskyy_held_a_meeting_with_Prime_Minister_of_Poland_Mateusz_Morawiecki_who_is_in_our_country_on_a_visit._52711473745.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221079%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22162702%2F1079px-President_of_Ukraine_Volodymyr_Zelenskyy_held_a_meeting_with_Prime_Minister_of_Poland_Mateusz_Morawiecki_who_is_in_our_country_on_a_visit._52711473745.jpg%201079w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22162702%2F1079px-President_of_Ukraine_Volodymyr_Zelenskyy_held_a_meeting_with_Prime_Minister_of_Poland_Mateusz_Morawiecki_who_is_in_our_country_on_a_visit._52711473745-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22162702%2F1079px-President_of_Ukraine_Volodymyr_Zelenskyy_held_a_meeting_with_Prime_Minister_of_Poland_Mateusz_Morawiecki_who_is_in_our_country_on_a_visit._52711473745-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674366%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPoland%20President%20Mateusz%20Morawiecki%20and%20Ukraine%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20during%20a%20meeting%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20February%2024%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20President%20Of%20Ukraine%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20message%20is%20very%20bad%2C%20both%20for%20Poland%E2%80%99s%20reputation%20but%20also%20because%20Poland%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20chief%20advocates%20of%20military%20aid%20to%20Ukraine.%20Saying%20Poland%20will%20not%20be%20sending%20more%20weapons%20means%20that%20Poland%C2%A0can%20no%20longer%20play%20this%20role%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Baranowski%2C%20managing%20director%20of%20Warsaw-based%20GMF%20East%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20German%20Marshall%20Fund%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20regard%20to%20Poland%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%20saying%20Warsaw%20would%20look%20at%20focusing%20on%20modernising%20its%20own%20forces%2C%20ahead%20of%20assisting%20Kyiv%2C%20Baranowski%20believes%20Poland%20is%20capable%20of%20modernising%20its%20military%20whilst%20continuing%20to%20help%20Ukraine%20in%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPoland%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20show%20firmness%20towards%20Kyiv%2C%20Baranowski%20remarked%2C%20should%20be%20understood%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20election%20campaign.%20Any%20solution%2C%20his%20GMF%20colleague%20Jazowska%20added%2C%20can%20only%20be%20found%20after%20Poland%E2%80%99s%20national%20election%20has%20concluded%20next%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoland%20a%20key%20transit%20country%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20sending%20its%20own%20supplies%20to%20Kyiv%2C%20Poland%20is%20also%20a%20key%20transit%20country%20for%20weaponry%