Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBhubaneswar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Political%20temperature%20in%20Odisha%20has%20shot%20up%20with%20the%20expulsion%20of%20media%20baron%20and%20Khandapada%20MLA%20Soumya%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%20from%20the%20ruling%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20on%20Thursday%2C%20September%2021.%20Though%20chief%20minister%20and%20BJD%20president%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20also%20expelled%20Remuna%20MLA%20Sudhansu%20Sekhar%20Parida%20for%20indulging%20in%20%E2%80%9Canti-people%E2%80%9D%20activities%2C%20the%20focus%20was%20clearly%20on%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%2C%20the%20son-in-law%20of%20former%20chief%20minister%20J.B.%20Patnaik%20and%20the%20high-profile%20owner%20of%20an%20Odia%20media%20conglomerate%20that%20runs%20a%20widely%20circulated%20vernacular%20daily%20and%20a%20popular%20news%20channel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20action%20against%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%2C%20who%20owns%20and%20edits%20the%20popular%20Odia%20daily%20%3Cem%3ESambad%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20comes%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20his%20removal%20from%20the%20post%20of%20BJD%20vice-president%20about%20a%20week%20ago.%20The%20Sambad%20office%20was%20recently%20raided%20by%20the%20Economic%20Offence%20Wing%20(EOW)%20of%20the%20state%20Crime%20Branch%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fothers%2Fodisha-eow-raids-office-of-newspaper-owned-by-soumya-patnaik-alleges-loan-fraud-101695213202175.html%5C%22%3Ecase%20of%20alleged%20loan%20fraud%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20raids%20followed%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%E2%80%99s%20write-ups%20in%20%3Cem%3ESambad%3C%2Fem%3E%20criticising%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20private%20secretary%20V.K.%20Pandian.%20The%20secretary%E2%80%99s%20style%20of%20functioning%20and%20his%20visits%20to%20various%20districts%20%E2%80%93%20where%20he%20was%20accorded%20more%20importance%20than%20elected%20representatives%20%E2%80%93%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fodisha-ias-officer-karthikeyan-pandian-naveen-patnaik-successor%5C%22%3Egarnered%3C%2Fa%3E%20interest%20and%20disdain%20in%20political%20circles.%20Opposition%20leaders%20feel%20that%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%20has%20been%20punished%20for%20%E2%80%9Cdaring%E2%80%9D%20to%20take%20on%20the%20most%20powerful%20bureaucrat%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERemuna%20MLA%20Sudhansu%20Sekhar%20Parida%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20was%20expelled%20after%20being%20accused%20of%20misappropriating%20government%20subsidies%20worth%20Rs%203%20crore%20meant%20for%20farmers.%20The%20matter%20is%20being%20investigated%20by%20the%20state%20vigilance%20wing.%20Parida%20not%20only%20denied%20the%20allegations%20but%20also%20asserted%20that%20the%20people%20of%20his%20constituency%20knew%20he%20was%20innocent.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20people%20of%20Remuna%20are%20with%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EParida%2C%20however%2C%20is%20small%20fish%20compared%20to%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%2C%20whose%20editorial%20comments%20sometimes%20embarrassed%20the%20BJD%20leadership.%20Things%20came%20to%20a%20head%20when%20he%20targeted%20Pandian%2C%20questioning%20his%20visits%20to%20districts%20which%20was%20seen%20as%20an%20act%20of%20appropriating%20the%20powers%20and%20duties%20of%20elected%20representatives.%20Most%20senior%20BJD%20leaders%20immediately%20sprang%20to%20the%20defence%20of%20Pandian%20and%20accused%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%20of%20%E2%80%9Cstabbing%20the%20party%20in%20the%20back%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20rift%20between%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%20and%20chief%20minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20widened%20after%20his%20removal%20from%20the%20post%20of%20BJD%20vice-president%20their%20relations%20worsened%20after%20EOW%20raided%20the%20office%20of%20Sambad%20on%20September%2018%20and%20grilled%20some%20senior%20officers%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20case%20of%20alleged%20fraud.%20The%20case%20was%20registered%20following%20a%20complaint%20by%20Aseem%20Mohapatra%2C%20a%20former%20employee%20of%20Sambad%5C%5CEastern%20Media%20Limited%20(EML)%2C%20the%20company%20which%20publishes%20the%20daily.%20Mohapatra%20alleged%20that%20EML%20had%20availed%20two%20loans%20of%20Rs%205%20lakh%20each%20in%20his%20name%20in%202009%20and%202015%2C%20for%20which%20he%20was%20forced%20to%20give%20his%20consent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20press%20release%20issued%20by%20the%20BJD%20on%20the%20expulsion%20of%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%20referred%20to%20the%20FIR%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmany%20ex-employees%20of%20Sambad%20newspaper%20have%20made%20similar%20allegations%20with%20the%20EOW%20Odisha.%20It%20is%20a%20serious%20case%20of%20organised%20bank%20fraud%20involving%20loans%20worth%20crores%20of%20rupees%20taken%20in%20the%20name%20of%20more%20than%20300%20employees%20of%20Sambad%20by%20using%20fraudulent%20means%20and%20forged%20documents.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F02133708%2FFyg_X-uaIAApRQR.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F02133708%2FFyg_X-uaIAApRQR.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F02133708%2FFyg_X-uaIAApRQR-300x207.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F02133708%2FFyg_X-uaIAApRQR-1024x707.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666267%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22829%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOdisha%20chief%20minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40naveen_odisha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOpposition%20parties%20slam%20BJD%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%20could%20not%20be%20reached%20for%20his%20reaction%20to%20the%20action%20against%20him%2C%20the%20two%20major%20opposition%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20Congress%20and%20BJP%20%E2%80%93%20described%20his%20expulsion%20as%20undemocratic%20and%20a%20sign%20of%20growing%20intolerance%20to%20criticism%20within%20the%20ruling%20BJD.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20absolutely%20no%20democracy%20in%20the%20BJD.%20The%20party%20leadership%20is%20not%20only%20intolerant%20but%20also%20scared%20of%20facing%20the%20truth.%20The%20action%20against%20Soumya%20Ranjan%20does%20not%20bode%20well%20for%20the%20party%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20BJP%20veteran%20and%20leader%20of%20opposition%20Jay%20Narayan%20Mishra.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EState%20Congress%20president%20Sarat%20Patnaik%20said%20the%20action%20against%20Soumya%20was%20clearly%20vindictive%20in%20nature.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20has%20been%20punished%20for%20telling%20the%20truth.%20The%20BJD%20continues%20to%20ignore%20the%20misdeeds%20of%20many%20of%20its%20leaders%20but%20it%20has%20acted%20against%20Soumya%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%20because%20it%20is%20scared%20of%20facing%20the%20truth%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERanjan%20Patnaik%20is%20not%20the%20only%20BJD%20leader%20to%20have%20been%20punished%20by%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20top%20brass%20for%20%E2%80%9Canti-people%20activities.%E2%80%9D%20Before%20him%2C%20Gopalpur%20MLA%20Pradeep%20Panigrahi%20faced%20the%20wrath%20of%20the%20BJD%20leadership.%20He%20was%20arrested%20on%20corruption%20charges%20and%20sent%20to%20jail.%20As%20he%20tried%20to%20fight%20back%2C%20he%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fodisha-expelled-bjd-mla-pradeep-panigrahi-arrested-on-job-fraud-charges-1746501-2020-12-03%5C%22%3Eexpelled%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20party%20in%20December%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBJD%20leaders%20who%20had%20criticised%20Ranjan%20Patnaik%20in%20the%20past%20refrained%20from%20commenting%20on%20his%20expulsion.%20It%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20clear%20that%20the%20party%20will%20not%20tolerate%20any%20attack%20either%20on%20the%20chief%20minister%20or%20those%20close%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERanjan%20Patnaik%2C%20on%20his%20part%2C%20had%20ignored%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20private%20secretary%20Pandian%20was%20undertaking%20visits%20to%20different%20districts%20to%20assess%20the%20progress%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20development%20projects%20with%20the%20express%20consent%20of%20his%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20what%20irked%20most%20opposition%20leaders%20was%20the%20kind%20of%20welcome%20he%20was%20accorded%20in%20the%20districts%20he%20visited.%20They%20felt%20that%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20appropriate%20what%20was%20actually%20their%20due.%20%E2%80%9CPoliticians%20have%20got%20so%20used%20to%20being%20welcomed%20in%20a%20grand%20manner%20by%20people%20and%20officials%20during%20their%20visits%20to%20their%20areas%20that%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20tolerate%20someone%20else%20receiving%20the%20same%20kind%20of%20treatment.%20This%20seems%20to%20have%20created%20the%20problem%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20political%20analyst%20Shashi%20Kant%20Mishra.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F20164226%2FFyGoeKCakAAfI4N.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F20164226%2FFyGoeKCakAAfI4N.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F20164226%2FFyGoeKCakAAfI4N-300x152.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F20164226%2FFyGoeKCakAAfI4N-1024x517.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-659170%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22606%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIAS%20officer%20V.%20Karthikeyan%20Pandian%E2%80%99s%20clout%20has%20been%20rising.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40swayam4Odisha%