p%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20step%20into%20the%20house%20today%2C%20everything%20around%20you%20changes.%20It%20isn%E2%80%99t%202023%20anymore%2C%20but%20you%20are%20transported%20back%20to%20the%20early%201900s.%20Everything%20from%20the%20flooring%20and%20the%20house%E2%80%99s%20layout%20to%20the%20furniture%20gives%20a%20glimpse%20of%20the%20bygone%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EModernising%20the%20house%20while%20preserving%20its%20authenticity%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBorn%20and%20raised%20in%20Kottayam%2C%20Kerala%2C%20the%2031-year-old%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20as%20a%20kid%2C%20I%20was%20very%20attracted%20to%20designing%20things%20and%20repurposing%20old%20objects.%20This%20interest%20later%20flourished%20into%20a%20passion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20her%20graduation%20in%20design%2C%20Anupa%20moved%20to%20the%20UK%20to%20get%20a%20master%E2%80%99s%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20love%20nature.%20I%20have%20always%20been%20inclined%20towards%20sustainable%20living%20and%20design.%20So%20doing%20a%20master%E2%80%99s%20in%20sustainable%20design%20looked%20like%20the%20right%20choice%20for%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20worked%20in%20the%20field%20for%20a%20while%20now%2C%20when%20it%20came%20to%20renovating%20her%20own%20house%2C%20she%20was%20sure%20about%20two%20things%20%E2%80%94%20to%20keep%20the%20house%20as%20authentic%20as%20possible%20and%20use%20sustainable%20means%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20sitting%20on%20a%203%2C000%20sq%20ft%20area%2C%20Pullolickel%20Veedu%20is%20an%20outstanding%20example%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F300504%2Fsustainable-home-in-kerala-made-with-old-stones-and-reused-wood-without-cutting-trees%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esustainability%20and%20traditionality.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3